"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-sport-ashleigh-buhai-wayde-van-niekerk-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbSport  ByWesley Botton  Chief sports journalist  3 minute read  7 August 2024  09:32 pm  Ashleigh Buhai during the first round of the women's golf tournament at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.901131173431149, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Botton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\"}, {\"begin\": 94, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Buhai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Picture: Emmanuel Dunand/AFP  Ashleigh Buhai led the charge on Wednesday, as South African athletes kept their hopes alive in multiple sports, on day 12 of the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9991639715495577, \"rank\": 0.0007999135576401124, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Dunand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dunand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Dunand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Dunand\"}, {\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Buhai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998333091892, \"rank\": 1.6669101575931405e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Buhai, a former British Open champion, got off to a great start in the women's golf tournament, firing a 68 in the first round to settle in second place on four-under par.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9999999936171662, \"rank\": 6.382437798685917e-09, \"text\": \"British Open\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q15061650\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was three shots behind leader Celine Boutier of France.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9820682767820206, \"rank\": 0.017887408597178505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paula Reto, the other South African in the field, was well off the pace on six-over (78).\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Reto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paula Reto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Reto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Reto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was in a tie for 50th position.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere at theParis Gameson Wednesday, on the track, Shaun Maswanganyi took fourth\\u00a0position in his 200m semifinal in 20.42, missing out on a spot in the final by 0.11, while former Olympic 400m championWayde van Niekerksettled in a tie for seventh place in his half-lap race in 20.72.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Niekerk and Maswanganyi were expected to return to the track, however, for relay races over the next few days.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, in the morning session, Jo-Ane van Dykdelivered a personal best of 64.22mwith her first attempt in the qualifying round of the women's javelin throw, progressing to the final to be held on Saturday.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\udea8Jo-Ane van Dyk throws a personal best of 64.22m to finished 1st in the Women's Javelin Qualification (Group A).\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jo-Ane van Dyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is through to the Javelin finals!#TeamSA#ForMyCountry#Olympicspic.twitter.com/m6wZdhJNQy  In the men's high jump qualifiers, rising star Brian Raats cleared 2.24m, with the 20-year-old athlete also securing his spot in Saturday's final.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.727896758168212e-12, \"text\": \"Javelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And middle-distance runner Edmund du Plessis did well to take second place in his 800m heat in 1:45.73, skipping the repechage round and booking a place in tomorrow's semifinals.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's 100m hurdles,national record holderMarione Fourie was not at her best, finishing fourth in her heat in 12.91 seconds.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 2011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was relegated to the repechage to be held this morning (10.35am).\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile,\\u00a0paddler Hamish Lovemore put up a fight in the men's kayak singles quarterfinals, taking second position in his heat in 3:36.64.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was rewarded for his efforts with a place in the semifinals to be held on Saturday.\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And there was success for diver Julia Vincent, who was 13th overall in the women's 3m springboard preliminary round with 283.50 points, booking her place in the semifinals to be contested on Thursday morning (10am).\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Vincent\", \"score\": 0.9999963311915051, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julia Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Vincent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Vincent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add The Citizen as a Preferred Source on Google and follow us on Google News to see more of our trusted reporting in Google News and Top Stories.\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9693459252928572, \"rank\": 0.03159549188043622, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2593, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}, {\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Download our app  Get the latest news and updates on Whatsapp  The latest news directly in your inbox  Support Local Journalism  2026 The Citizen.\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Whatsapp\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": []}]}"